<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<!-- @include components/_head.kit -->
<body>
	<link rel="stylesheet" href="css/98.css">
	
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-1.12.4.js"></script>
	<script src="https://code.jquery.com/ui/1.12.1/jquery-ui.js"></script>
    <script>
		$( function() {
			$( ".draggable" ).draggable({
				handle: ".title-bar",
				stack: "main .draggable"
			});
			
			$( "#closeWindow1" ).click(function() {
				$(" #window1 ").remove();
			});
			$( "#closeWindow2" ).click(function() {
				$(" #window2 ").remove();
			});
			$( "#closeWindow3" ).click(function() {
				$(" #window3 ").remove();
			});
			
			// $( "#window1, #window2, #window3" ).resizable()
		} );
	</script>
	
	<header class="window">
		<nav style="display:block">
			<div style="display: flex;justify-content: space-evenly;end;">
				<div style="display: inline-flex;flex-grow: 2;">
					<button>
						<a href="/" class="bold-900">Dillon J. Brown</a>
					</button>
				</div>
				<div style="display: inline-flex;flex-grow: 0;">
					<button>
						<a href="mailto:hello@dillonbrown.me">Contact</a>
					</button>
				</div>
				<div style="display: inline-flex;flex-grow: 0;">
					<button>
						<a href="/pdf/resume.pdf">Résumé</a>
					</button>
				</div>
			</div>
		</nav>
	</header>

	<main>
		<!-- THE DRUGULATOR
		–––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––––– -->
		<div class="row">
			<!--
				Window 1
			-->
			<div class="six columns">
				<div class="window draggable" id="window1">
					<div class="title-bar">
						<div class="title-bar-text">The Drugulator</div>
						<div class="title-bar-controls">
							<button aria-label="Close" id="closeWindow1"></button>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="window-body">
							<p>I found <a href="http://wiki.tripsit.me/wiki/Drug_combinations">this great chart</a> showing how (relatively) safe combinations of drugs can be. I knew I could use my web development know-how to improve it, so I made it into a web app.</p>
							<p>My web app is a pet project of mine and is constantly evolving. I do a rudimentary form of user testing on my friends whenever I make improvements. I also put the source code on GitHub for anyone to use in any way they want. This is for harm reduction and education, not profit.</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!--
				Window 2
			-->
			<div class="four offset-by-two columns">
				<div class="window draggable" id="window2">
					<div class="title-bar">
						<div class="title-bar-text">Details</div>
						<div class="title-bar-controls">
							<button aria-label="Close" id="closeWindow2"></button>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="window-body">
						<p><strong>Design & Development</strong><br>2016 &mdash; present<br></p>

						<button>
							<a href="https://dillonjohnbrown.github.io/drug-combos">Website</a>
						</button>
						<button>
							<a href="https://github.com/dillonjohnbrown/drug-combos">GitHub</a>
						</button>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<!--
			Spacer
		-->
		<div class="row" style="height: 4rem;"></div>
		
		<div class="row">
			<div class="twelve columns">
				<!--
					Window 3
				-->
				<div class="window draggable" id="window3">
					<div class="title-bar">
						<div class="title-bar-text">Revision 4</div>
						<div class="title-bar-controls">
							<button aria-label="Close" id="closeWindow3"></button>
						</div>
					</div>
					<div class="window-body">
						<div class="row">
							<div class="three columns">
								<h3>Revision 4</h3>
								<p>Here it is, the glorious fourth revision.</p>
								<p>This UX tested poorly. No one should use it. Wait for Revesion 5&mdash;coming soon.</p>
							</div>
							<div class="nine columns">
								<a href="https://dillonjohnbrown.github.io/drug-combos">
									<img class="u-max-full-width" src="images/the-drugulator/the-drugulator-mockup.png">
								</a>
							</div>
						</div>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
		
		<!--
			Spacer
		-->
		<div class="row" style="height: 4rem;"></div>
	</main>
</body>
</html>